description: Lists all associated origination identities in your pool. If you specify filters, the output includes information for only those origination identities that meet the filter criteria.

parameters.name: PoolId
parameters.description: The unique identifier for the pool. This value can be either the PoolId or PoolArn.

parameters.name: Filters
parameters.description: An array of PoolOriginationIdentitiesFilter objects to filter the results.. (dict) --- Information about origination identities associated with a pool that meets a specified criteria. The name of the attribute to filter on. An array values to filter for. (string) ---

nested_params.name: Name
nested_params.description: The name of the attribute to filter on.

nested_params.name: Values
nested_params.description: An array values to filter for.

nested_items.name: PoolArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the pool.

nested_items.name: PoolId
nested_items.description: The unique PoolId of the pool.

nested_items.name: OriginationIdentities
nested_items.description: An array of any OriginationIdentityMetadata objects.

nested_items.name: OriginationIdentityArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) associated with the origination identity.

nested_items.name: OriginationIdentity
nested_items.description: The unique identifier of the origination identity.

nested_items.name: IsoCountryCode
nested_items.description: The two-character code, in ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 format, for the country or region.

nested_items.name: NumberCapabilities
nested_items.description: Describes if the origination identity can be used for text messages, voice calls or both.

nested_items.name: PhoneNumber
nested_items.description: The phone number in E.164 format.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: The token to be used for the next set of paginated results. If this field is empty then there are no more results.
